name: "Transpacific Comfort" -CD
description:
In Speed The Band's debut album release, the family band based in two different states and across an ocean (hence the title), brings listeners a post-modern twist on 90's-style folk-rock. Classic songwriting and guitar licks coupled with the soft, yet powerful crooning by Carrie Speed Owsley give this record a heart and soul of its own. Transpacific Comfort spans the musical palette by offering fun-loving pop tracks reminiscent of early Beatles tunes to passionate love songs full of substance to cause-driven-power-ballads. This release is poised to become a Winter favorite with songs for all occasions, earning it the classification of a classic album.

Track Listing:

1. Angelina Dreams (Carrie's Version)
2. Her Three Words
3. Married a Monster
4. Chelsea Runs
5. Hey You
6. The Girl Inside
7. Home

13. She
